# Vulture whitelist for Stronghold.
#
# Many "unused" findings come from framework-mediated indirection that
# Vulture cannot trace at static-analysis time:
#   - FastAPI route handlers bound via @router.{get,post,...} decorators
#   - DI-wired protocol implementations (agents, registries, stores)
#   - uvicorn --factory entrypoints (create_app)
#   - Protocol method parameters in stubs where the body is `...`
#   - Abstract tool executors and strategy subclasses
#
# This file is generated via `vulture src/stronghold/ --make-whitelist`
# and committed as the CI baseline. New dead code WILL fail the Vulture
# job because it won't be in this whitelist. Regenerate with:
#
#   vulture src/stronghold/ --make-whitelist > .vulture_whitelist.py
#
# — and audit the diff: new entries may be real dead code, not false
# positives. Classify each before expanding the whitelist.

